  { :name => "One Inch Badge presents: HAIM @ The Haunt, Brighton", :longitude => -0.137163, :latitude => 50.82253000000001, :gmaps => true, :description => "TICKETS: http://www.seetickets.com/Event/HAIM/The-Haunt/662299 // http://www.wegottickets.com/event/183605 // www.ticketweb.co.uk // www.gigantic.com // Resident Music (01273 606312)\n\nSUNDAY NOVEMBER 18th // SUNDAY NOVEMBER 18th//\n\nOne Inch Badge presents:\n\nHAIM\nThe “three sisters and a mister” consists of three San Fernando Valley sisters Danielle, Alana, and Este Haim, and unrelated ʻmisterʼ, drummer Dash Hutton. The Forever EP, already a free download through their websitemerges the spirit of Fleetwood Mac with touches of 90s RnB. It sounds fresh,it sounds exciting, and yet it gives only the merest glimpse of what these ladies can do live.\n\nThe sisters grew up playing classic rock songs with their parents in a family band called ʻRockinhaimʼ, and having struck out on their own, the acclaim has spread quickly. And whilst Danielle Haim toured the world as drummer and guitarist for Julian Casablancas, her sisters were studying back in LA, where Este recently completed a degree at UCLA in Brazilian music.\n\nWithout doubt one of the most exciting new bands of 2012, this show is show is set to be very incredible indeed...\n\n+ DEATH AT SEA\nLiverpool's Death At Sea sets their sails towards a 90s, Sub Pop-like sound\n\n+KILL MOON\nFemale fronted powerful 3 piece. BIG chorus : BIG ambition\n\nSUNDAY 18th NOVEMBER 2012\nat The Haunt\n10 Pool Valley Coach Station, Brighton, BN1 1NJ\n£7.00 advance // 7:30pm // 14+\n\nTICKETS: http://www.seetickets.com/Event/HAIM/The-Haunt/662299 // http://www.wegottickets.com/event/183605 // www.ticketweb.co.uk // www.gigantic.com // Resident Music (01273 606312)\n\nwww.oneinchbadge.com\n\nOTHER UP-COMING SHOWS FROM ONE INCH BADGE:\n\n7th November: Holograms @ Green Door Store, Brighton\n7th November: Mystery Jets @ Concorde 2, Brighton\n12th November: LA Shark @ Green Door S